ers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."]},{"name":"Mared","meanings":["Simplified form of   Marged ."]}]},{"name":"ferch","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["German: variant of   Ferg  . Compare   Verch  .","Probably also an Americanized form of German <b>Förtsch</b> (see   Foertsch  ).","Probably also an Americanized form of German <b>Förch</b> (see   Foerch  )."],"variants":[{"name":"Ferg","meanings":["1  ‘Sharp blade’.","2  ‘Wind’."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Margred ferch Rhys was born about 1382, in Cardiganshire, Wales as the daughter of Rhys \" Llwyd\" ap Rhys. She married Rhys ap Gruffudd about 1400, in Wales, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 2 sons."},"et":{"about 1382–":"umbes 1382–Surnud","1382–Female":"1382–Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","1382–Male":"1382–Surnud","1400–Male":"1400–Surnud","1430–Male":"1430–Surnud","1355–1450":"1355–1450","about 1382":"umbes 1382","ABT    1430":"umbes 1430","1400":"1400","1355":"1355","1430":"1430","about 1400":"umbes 1400","1450":"1450","1382":"1382","Wales, United Kingdom":"Wales, United Kingdom","of Rhuddallt,Llanbeblig,Caernarvonshire,Wales":"Llanbeblig, Caernarfonshire, Wales, United Kingdom","Gloddaith, Caernarfonshire, Wales":"Gloddaith, Caernarfonshire, Wales","of Ffrydmor,Is Coed,Cardiganshire,Wales":"Cardiganshire, Wales"},"fi":{"about 1382–":"noin 1382–Kuollut","1382–Female":"1382–Kuollut","–Male":"Kuollut","1382–Male":"1382–Kuollut","1400–Male":"1400–Kuollut","1430–Male":"1430–Kuollut","1355–1450":"1355–1450","about 1382":"noin 1382","ABT    1430":"noin 1430","1400":"1400","